1 unit Lime
¼ ounce Cilantro
10 ounce Ground Pork
1 unit Green Bell Pepper
1 ounce Sweet Thai Chili Sauce
4 tablespoon Sweet Soy Glaze
1 unit Microwavable Lemongrass Brown Rice
1 tablespoon Cornstarch
½ teaspoon Sugar
2 teaspoon Cooking Oil
1 tablespoon Butter
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry all produce.
• Zest and quarter lime. Core, deseed, and dice bell pepper
into ½-inch pieces. Finely chop cilantro.
• In a small bowl, combine chili sauce, sweet soy glaze,
¼ cup water, 1 tsp cornstarch (we sent more), ½ tsp sugar,
and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. (For 4 servings, use
1⁄3 cup water, 2 tsp cornstarch, and 1 tsp sugar.)

• Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper; season with salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until slightly tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add pork* and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes. Season with
salt and pepper.
• Stir in sweet chili glaze; cook, stirring, until pork is coated,
30-60 seconds more.

• Meanwhile, gently massage rice in package to break up
grains. Partially open package; place 1 TBSP butter
inside. (For 4 servings, use 1 TBSP butter per package.)
Microwave according to package instructions, 90 seconds.
• Carefully open package fully; season rice with salt and
pepper. Transfer to a medium bowl and add half the
cilantro and lime zest to taste. Fluff with a fork.

• Divide rice between bowls and top with pork and pepper
mixture and remaining cilantro. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.